article.headline: Pennsylvania 60, Princeton 41
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Steve Danley scored 18 points and Ibrahim Jaaber added 17 as Penn overcame Princeton's definitive style to defeat the Tigers 60-41 Tuesday night. Mark Zoller scored 15 points and had 10 rebounds for the Quakers (15-6, 7-0 Ivy League). Penn remained the only undefeated team in the Ivy League. Luke Owings hit a season-high 18 points for Princeton and Scott Greenman added 14 for the Tigers (7-13, 5-2), who saw a four-game winning streak snapped. The game was tied 8-8 with 9:37 left in the first half when Zoller scored eight points in a 15-5 run that gave the Quakers a 23-13 halftime advantage. Penn led 32-20 with 13:24 left, and the Tigers got no closer than 40-30, on a three-point play by Owings, with 10:30 remaining. Jaaber made a lay-up, and Danley had two free throws as Penn pulled away. Jaaber, the team's all-time steals leader, had four in the game to increase his season total to a league-leading 73.
